[[全球采取行动组织|全球采取行动组织]]帮助协调34名国际记者进入叙利亚战区，包括在霍姆斯被困期间死亡的摄影记者[[雷米·奥奇利克|雷米·奥奇利克]]和记者[[玛丽·科尔文|玛丽·科尔文]]，以及严重受伤的记者伊迪斯·鲍威尔。2月28日，为了帮助摄影记者康洛伊从[[霍姆斯城|霍姆斯城]]撤退，该组织与反对运动人士共同筹划这起撤离行动。同时他们还帮助40名重伤者从巴巴艾默撤退，并送去了医疗援助物资。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.qq.com/a/20120301/000057.htm|title=叙利亚“敢死队”送受伤记者出境遭阻击13人死|accessdate=2015-05-28|archive-date=2015-05-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150528135815/http://news.qq.com/a/20120301/000057.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>全球采取行动组织组成了200人的行动网络，并为全球媒体提供影像资料。

==== 国际特赦组织 ====
[[国际特赦组织|国际特赦组织]]谴责针对“人民和平抗议活动”的“暴力镇压”，并要求释放政治囚犯。<ref>{{Cite news | title = Amnesty Condemns Syrian Crackdown on Protest | author =  | url = http://uk.news.yahoo.com/22/20110317/tpl-uk-syria-protest-amnesty-81f3b62.html | agency = Reuters (via Yahoo! News) | date =  | accessdate = 17 March 2011 | archive-url = http://web.archive.bibalex.org/web/20110319202720/http://uk.news.yahoo.com/22/20110317/tpl-uk-syria-protest-amnesty-81f3b62.html | archive-date = 2011-03-19 | dead-url = yes }}</ref>2011年7月6日，该组织一名发言人宣称他有证据证明叙利亚政府在北部小镇特尔卡拉有违反人权行为。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://english.aljazeera.net/news/middleeast/2011/07/201175202656973422.html|agency=Al Jazeera English|date=6 July 2011|accessdate=6 July 2011|title=Syria accused of crimes against humanity|archive-date=2011-09-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110906031130/http://english.aljazeera.net/news/middleeast/2011/07/201175202656973422.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==== 红十字国际委员会 ====
2012年1月21日，[[红十字国际委员会|红十字国际委员会]]督促叙利亚当局和冲突各方每日停火一定时间，以保证人道救援的进入。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.icrc.org/eng/resources/documents/news-release/2012/syria-news-2012-02-21.htm |title=Urgent call for daily halts in fighting |publisher=ICRC |date=21 February 2012 |accessdate=2015-05-28 |archive-date=2015-03-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150331094643/https://www.icrc.org/eng/resources/documents/news-release/2012/syria-news-2012-02-21.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>红十字国际委员会同样呼吁冲突各方始终保证区分平民和战斗参与者，并充分尊重国际人道法。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icrc.org/chi/resources/documents/article/editorial/2014-02-15-syria-maurer-humanitarian-principles.htm|title=国际人道法与人道原则不容协商——叙利亚也不例外|publisher=红十字国际委员会|accessdate=2015-05-28|archive-date=2015-05-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150528115532/https://www.icrc.org/chi/resources/documents/article/editorial/2014-02-15-syria-maurer-humanitarian-principles.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>2012年9月3日，红十字国际委员会主席[[彼得·毛雷尔|彼得·毛雷尔]]前往叙利亚进行为期三天的访问，以增强红十字国际委员会和叙利亚阿拉伯红新月会的人道主义应对能力。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.icrc.org/eng/resources/documents/news-release/2012/syria-news-2012-09-03.htm |title=Syria: ICRC president in Damascus |publisher=Icrc.org |date= |accessdate=2012-10-06 |archive-date=2012-10-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121008011421/http://www.icrc.org/eng/resources/documents/news-release/2012/syria-news-2012-09-03.htm |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite web |url=http://www.icrc.org/eng/resources/documents/news-release/2012/syria-news-2012-09-07.htm |title=Syria: ICRC president concludes visit amid relentless fighting |publisher=Icrc.org |date= |accessdate=2012-10-06 |archive-date=2012-10-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121021045130/http://www.icrc.org/eng/resources/documents/news-release/2012/syria-news-2012-09-07.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icrc.org/chi/resources/documents/photo-gallery/2012/syria-president-maurer-photo-gallery-2012-0.htm|title=叙利亚：红十字国际委员会主席彼得•毛雷尔访问叙利亚的照片集|publisher=红十字国际委员会|accessdate=2015-05-28|archive-date=2015-05-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150528115501/https://www.icrc.org/chi/resources/documents/photo-gallery/2012/syria-president-maurer-photo-gallery-2012-0.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==== 人权观察 ====
人权观察组织指出，在射杀自由发声的公民方面叙利亚政府显得毫不犹豫。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rferl.org/content/rights_groups_condemn_syria/2345012.html |title=Rights Groups Condemn Syria's Violent Crackdown On Protesters |publisher=RFE/RL |date=21 March 2011 |accessdate=2011-04-10 |archive-date=2011-03-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110326111620/http://www.rferl.org/content/rights_groups_condemn_syria/2345012.html |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite web |url=http://www.hrw.org/en/news/2011/03/20/syria-government-crackdown-leads-protester-deaths |title=Syria: Government Crackdown Leads to Protester Deaths |publisher=Human Rights Watch |date=20 March 2011 |accessdate=2011-04-10 |archive-date=2011-04-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110410201807/http://www.hrw.org/en/news/2011/03/20/syria-government-crackdown-leads-protester-deaths |dead-url=no }}</ref>他们认为，该政府的行为可以被认作是一种违反人权的犯罪。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.aljazeera.net/news/middleeast/2011/06/201161184642132562.html |title=Syrian abuses are 'crimes against humanity' |publisher=Al Jazeera |date=1 April 2011 |accessdate=2 April 2011 |archive-date=2011-09-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110903025213/http://english.aljazeera.net/news/middleeast/2011/06/201161184642132562.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>人权观察中东与北非分会负责人惠特森表示，在内战之前，叙利亚已经是“一个垂死的国家，我们不能进行新闻报道……事实是，我们需要通过报道记录政府的镇压活动和滥用职权的罪行。”

==== 罗马尼亚叙利亚自由社区（FSCR） ====
2011年6月，一个非盈利组织，罗马尼亚的叙利亚自由社区成立，以保护叙利亚文化遗产、维护居住在罗马尼亚的叙利亚人的权益为使命。<ref>{{ro icon}} [http://www.sirialibera.ro/rom/index.php?action=article&id_menu=12&id_article=94 "Cine suntem noi?"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.sirialibera.ro/rom/index.php?action=article&id_menu=12&id_article=94 |date=20130501021434 }}, ''Sirialibera.ro''</ref>在冲突一开始，FSCR立即组织行动，在土耳其-叙利亚边界的难民营内提供医疗援助和食物。<ref>{{ro icon}}[http://www.sirialibera.ro/rom/index.php?action=article&id_menu=14 "Dăruiește speranța. FII EROUL LOR! –campanie umanitară pentru copiii refugiați"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.sirialibera.ro/rom/index.php?action=article&id_menu=14 |date=20130501022854 }}, ''Sirialibera.ro''</ref>

